File: Former President Jacob Zuma. JOHANNESBURG - Former President Jacob Zuma surprised crowds with an impromptu performance during his daughters graduation ceremony at the University of Zululand. The proud father broke into song and dance at the ceremony on Thursday night as Brumelda Zuma graduated with a bachelor’s degree in administration. READ: Duduzane Zuma trial postponed Taking to social media Zuma described the joyous occasion as a 'special day' and said he could not help but join in with students as they celebrated their qualifications. "Today was a special day. My daughter Brumelda graduated from the University of Zululand. I couldn’t help but join the choir in jubilation", said Zuma.